Rachel DeHart Who are we as christians to decide what others believe? We don't know what others believe, even if they state that they are a certain denomination. I have known quite a few catholics that have a stronger relationship with Christ than many Christians I know. Just because someone chooses catholic as a label doesn't give anyone the right to judge them by that label. It is between Christ and that person - no one else.

Julie Beeman @Patio daddio - Catholics are true Christians. And you can't be "merely Catholic". One either follows the teachings of the Church or they don't. Have you read any of Dr. Scott Hahn's books? He is a former Presbyterian minister and biblical scholar who, after studying the scripture and actually studying Catholic theology, converted to Catholicism. Many find that his writings answer their questions and clarify miunderstandings about Catholic beliefs and doctrine.
